		<div class="card-container">
			<div class="card click" data-direction="left">
				  
          <div class="front News"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://www.valleylibrary.ca/sites/default/files/styles/featured_event/public/news-images/LA-seed-tile2.jpg?itok=b99gPKfN" width="140" height="140" alt="Seed library" /><h3 class="featured-event-location"></h3><h2 class="featured-event-title">Lawrencetown Seed Library</h2></div>    
          <div class="back News"><div class="featured-events-back-wrapper"><h3 class="featured-event-location"></h3><h2 class="featured-event-title">Lawrencetown Seed Library</h2><h4 class="featured-event-date"><div class="featured-event-day"></div><div class="featured-event-time"></div></h4><p class="featured-event-info">Welcome to our Seed Library Pilot Project!
● Need seeds to finish planting your vegetable garden?
● Perhaps growing vegetables is new to you?
● Looking for a family project that leads to healthy food choices and sustainable communities? We can help!
Pick up a packet of seeds for FREE from the Dr. Frank W. Morse Memorial Library in Lawrencetown, accompanied by planting instructions.
It’s as easy as 1-2-3.
1. Browse the seed packets, and decide what you’d like to grow.
2. Show us your library card.
3. We’ll give you the seeds!
If you need some inspiration, we've put together a BOOKLIST to help you get your plants in the ground.
Optional: As your project progresses, we’d love to receive updates. Send us a photo or message on Facebook, Instagram, or Twitter. Talk with staff if you’d like to give us permission for follow-up on the future of this, or other, seed projects.
Seeds kindly donated by: Hope Seeds; Annapolis Seeds; Paul Gregory, Organic Backyard Gardener
May 5, 2016: Read this great article in the Spectator about our seed library !
</p></div><a href="/news/lawrencetown-seed-library" class="featured-event-link">Learn More <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a></div>  			</div>
