			<div class="card click" data-direction="left">
				  
          <div class="front Event"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://www.valleylibrary.ca/sites/default/files/styles/featured_event/public/event_images/BUGlogo%20tile_5.png?itok=ChCCoKff" width="140" height="140" alt="" /><h3 class="featured-event-location">Bridgetown &amp; Area Library</h3><h2 class="featured-event-title">Bridgetown Ukulele Group</h2></div>    
          <div class="back Event"><div class="featured-events-back-wrapper"><h3 class="featured-event-location">Bridgetown &amp; Area Library</h3><h2 class="featured-event-title">Bridgetown Ukulele Group</h2><h4 class="featured-event-date"><div class="featured-event-day"><span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2016-05-09T19:00:00-03:00">May 9th (Mon)</span></div><div class="featured-event-time"><span class="date-display-single"><span class="date-display-start" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2016-05-09T19:00:00-03:00">7:00pm</span> to <span class="date-display-end" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2016-05-09T20:30:00-03:00">8:30pm</span></span></div></h4><p class="featured-event-info">The Bridgetown Ukulele Group meets on the second Monday of the month at the Bridgetown and Area Library. We play and sing together and share our enthusiasm for all things ukulele. No experience necessary, but a willingness to have fun is required.
No uke? No problem! We've got extras.
This free program is open to anyone aged 16 and over.
If you have any questions, email us at valleyukulele@gmail.com
</p></div><a href="/event/bridgetown-ukulele-group-6" class="featured-event-link">Learn More <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a></div>  			</div>
