			<div class="card click" data-direction="left">
				  
          <div class="front Event"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://www.valleylibrary.ca/sites/default/files/styles/featured_event/public/event_images/BR%20digital%20media%20tile.png?itok=AzKcXKVk" width="140" height="140" alt="" /><h3 class="featured-event-location">Bridgetown &amp; Area Library</h3><h2 class="featured-event-title">The Impact of Digital Media</h2></div>    
          <div class="back Event"><div class="featured-events-back-wrapper"><h3 class="featured-event-location">Bridgetown &amp; Area Library</h3><h2 class="featured-event-title">The Impact of Digital Media</h2><h4 class="featured-event-date"><div class="featured-event-day"><span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2016-05-10T19:00:00-03:00">May 10th (Tue)</span></div><div class="featured-event-time"><span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2016-05-10T19:00:00-03:00">7:00pm</span></div></h4><p class="featured-event-info">Join Raphael Foshay for a presentation and discussion about the impact of digital media and the internet on learning.  What are the implications of digital media for intelligence and the way we interact with information?  Have machines altered our identity?  What opportunities are emerging, and what challenges do we face?
Raphael Foshay teaches in Athabasca University's MA Program in Integrated Studies.  He is the editor of The Digital Nexus: Identity, Agency and Political Engagement.
Registration is required. Please call the branch during open hours at 902-665-2758 to reserve your spot or register below. 
</p></div><a href="/event/impact-digital-media" class="featured-event-link">Learn More <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a></div>  			</div>
